; Regression test for issue #697: --dc has a problem with -V and -B (BZ#697)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/697
; --dc with -B crashes: get_at() fails because -B converts commodity amounts to
; plain amounts, but the --dc format tries to index into them as sequences.

P 2015/01/01 AAPL $100.00
P 2015/06/01 AAPL $150.00

2015/01/15 Buy stock
    Assets:Investments    10 AAPL @ $100.00
    Assets:Cash          $-1000.00

test bal --dc -B -> 1
__ERROR__
While evaluating value expression:
  ansify_if(justify(scrub(abs((get_at(display_total, 1) | 0))), 14, (((14 + 1) + int(prepend_width)) + int(total_width)), true, color), (should_bold ? (bold : null)))
While calling function 'get_at (0, 1)':
While calling function 'abs <#EXPR (get_at(display_total, {1}) | {0})>':
While calling function 'scrub <#EXPR abs((get_at(display_total, {1}) | {0}))>':
While calling function 'justify (<#EXPR scrub(abs((get_at(display_total, {1}) | {0})))>, <#EXPR {14}>, <#EXPR ((({14} + {1}) + int(prepend_width)) + int(total_width))>, 1, 0)':
While calling function 'ansify_if (<#EXPR justify(scrub(abs((get_at(display_total, {1}) | {0}))), {14}, ((({14} + {1}) + int(prepend_width)) + int(total_width)), true, color)>, )':
Error: Attempting to get argument at index 1 from an integer
end test
